variable.name: ASCSOURCE
variable.comment: Ascertainment Source This file has one row for every form 130 or 122 recording in situ or invasive breast cancer outcome(s). A participant may have more than one of these forms. Only the first occurrence of each outcome is counted, e.g. Limiting the file to rows where BREASTINV=1 will find a single row for each participant with a invasive breast cancer outcome.

variable.name: BREASTINV
variable.comment: Defined as a breast cancer from a Death or the first adjudication where the form 122 or 130 details indicate an invasive cancer. Breast Cancer Invasive is adjudicated for CT and OS participants. WHI adjudicated all reports of breast cancer for a ppt until the first invasive Breast Cancer. i.e. The first Invasive Breast Cancer may not be the first Breast Cancer. This file does not include cancers determined solely by the cause of death.

variable.name: BREASTINSITU
variable.comment: Defined as the first breast cancer where the form 122 or 130 details indicate an in situ cancer. Breast Cancer In Situ is adjudicated for CT and OS participants. Breast Cancer In Situ occurring on or after a Breast Cancer Invasive is not counted.

variable.name: ICDCODE
variable.comment: All centrally adjudicated cancers (F130) have an ICD-O-2 code. The only locally adjudicated cancers with a code are those marked as 'other' on F122. F122 codes do not include a decimal. See the SEER coding section of the data prep/use document for details. A description of the ICD site codes can be found in the reference file seer_icd_site_codes.dat by merging on the ICDCODE variable.

variable.name: GRADING
variable.comment: Morphology: 6th digit WHI used SEER 1988, 2nd edition rules when coding cancers, see the SEER coding section of the data prep/use document for details.

variable.name: SIZE
variable.comment: Evidence of Disease (SEER): digits 1-3 When size doesnt make sense, this field is used for other purposes (e.g. Leukemias have no size, this field records AIDS status). Size is usually measured in mm, though it may vary by cancer type. Even for cancers that do have a size, not all values indicate an actual size (e.g. 2 for many cancers means '<=2mm', but for breast cancer it means 'Mammographic diagnosis only, tumor not clinically palpable' ). WHI used the SEER 1988, 2nd edition rules for coding cancers. See the SEER coding section of the data prep/use document for details.
